  Athi River Mining Ltd. (ARML) ,  Kenya â€™s
second-biggest cement maker by market value, declined for a
third day this week.  The stock lost 1 shilling, or 0.6 percent, to 170 shillings
at the 3 p.m. close in Nairobi, after gaining as much as 1.2
percent in earlier trading today.  Profit for the year rose to 792 million shillings ($9.2
million) in 2010 from 645 million shillings in the year-earlier
period, the company said yesterday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
